function count_model_rows(df_cars)
    return groupby(df_cars, :model) |> mapreduce(x -> (x[1] => length(x)), mergewith(_combine, Dict()))
end
```

This function groups the data by the `:model` column and then applies a map-reduce operation to count the number of rows for each model. The resulting output is a dictionary where the keys are the distinct models and the values are the counts of how many times each model appears in the data frame.
